Privacy Policy

Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how BookMind AI handles your information.

⸻

Information Collection

BookMind AI does not require account creation and does not directly collect personal information such as name, email address, or phone number.

All books, ratings, notes, and preferences entered by the user are stored locally on the device and are not uploaded to our servers.

⸻

Local Data Storage

All user-generated content, including books, ratings, notes, and preferences, is stored only on the user’s device.

We do not use cloud storage or external servers to store this data.

⸻

Advertising (Third-Party Services)

BookMind AI displays banner and interstitial advertisements using Google AdMob, a third-party advertising service.

AdMob may automatically collect certain device-level information, such as:
	•	Device identifiers (e.g., advertising identifier)
	•	Ad interaction and usage data

This data may be used by Google for:
	•	Displaying advertisements
	•	Measuring ad performance
	•	Fraud prevention and security

We do not have access to or control over the data collected by Google AdMob.

Users may permanently remove all ads by purchasing the “Remove Ads” one-time in-app purchase.

⸻

AI Recommendations

The app may use an AI-powered feature to generate book recommendations based on in-app preferences and interactions.
	•	No personally identifiable information is stored by us
	•	AI recommendations are generated without creating user profiles
	•	No personal data is sold or shared by us for AI processing

⸻

Data Usage

Data is used only to:
	•	Provide core app functionality
	•	Display advertisements
	•	Improve app stability and performance
	•	Generate AI-powered book recommendations

⸻

Data Sharing

We do not sell or trade user data.

Limited data may be processed by third-party services (such as Google AdMob) solely for advertising and analytics purposes, in accordance with their privacy policies.

⸻

App Tracking Transparency

BookMind AI complies with Apple’s App Tracking Transparency (ATT) framework.

Where required, users are asked for permission before tracking-related data is accessed. Users can manage their tracking preferences at any time through their device settings.

⸻

Data Security

All user-generated data is stored locally on the device.

Reasonable technical measures are taken to protect the app and ensure data security.

⸻

Children’s Privacy

BookMind AI does not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13.

If you believe a child has provided personal information, please contact us so appropriate action can be taken.

⸻

Changes to This Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time.
Any changes will be reflected within the app or on the App Store product page.

⸻

Contact

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact:

Email: 6353ww@gmail.com

⸻

